<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,1457,1883]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">
This species appeared to be a manuscript name because it was not described in 
<bibRefCitation author="Engel" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" refString="Engel, E. O. (1937) 25. Bombyliidae. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der Palaearktischen Region. E. Schweizerbartische Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, band IV / 3, 561 - 619." type="book chapter" year="1937">
Engel (
<number box="[273,334,1497,1523]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" value="1937.0">1937</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
or included in his index. However, it is included in his key (p. 
<number box="[1089,1138,1497,1523]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" value="572.0">572</number>
). This validates the name, which was overlooked by Steyskal &amp; El Bialy (
<number box="[998,1059,1537,1563]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" value="1967.0">1967</number>
) and by 
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Greathead, D. J. (1999) World Catalog of Bee flies (Diptera: Bombyliidae). Backhuys Publishers, Leiden, xlvii + 756 pp." type="book" year="1999">
Evenhuis &amp; Greathead (
<number box="[406,470,1577,1603]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. No 
<typeStatus box="[544,595,1577,1603]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">type</typeStatus>
material was designated but a single male specimen, with Engel's identification label was found in 
<collectionCode box="[753,818,1617,1643]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/e8gh-2tfg" name="Cairo University" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">CUE</collectionCode>
*. Since there is the possibility that further specimens seen by Engel may exist elsewhere the specimen in 
<collectionCode box="[994,1056,1657,1683]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/e8gh-2tfg" name="Cairo University" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">CUE</collectionCode>
* is a 
<typeStatus box="[1120,1214,1657,1683]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">syntype</typeStatus>
, which is here designated 
<typeStatus box="[454,566,1697,1723]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,1457,1883]" lastBlockId="4.[264,1323,284,670]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName authority="Becker (1916)" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1916" box="[312,639,1737,1763]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albida">
<emphasis box="[312,454,1737,1762]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">Villa albida</emphasis>
Becker (
<number box="[569,630,1737,1763]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" value="1916.0">1916</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[903,1006,1737,1763]" name="Hungary" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">Hungary</collectingCountry>
and is listed for 
<collectingCountry box="[1227,1281,1737,1763]" name="Italy" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">Italy</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis" box="[264,640,1777,1803]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Greathead, D. J. (1999) World Catalog of Bee flies (Diptera: Bombyliidae). Backhuys Publishers, Leiden, xlvii + 756 pp." type="book" year="1999">
Evenhuis &amp; Greathead (
<number box="[567,631,1777,1803]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[717,820,1777,1803]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">holotype</typeStatus>
male (
<collectingCountry box="[913,1006,1777,1803]" name="Hungary" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">Ungarn</collectingCountry>
, Sajo.) from 
<collectionCode box="[1178,1263,1777,1803]" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">ZMHB</collectionCode>
was examined. The Egyptian specimen (
<taxonomicName box="[687,849,1817,1842]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aegyptiaca">
<emphasis box="[687,849,1817,1842]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">V.aegyptiaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) differs from it and the description of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="24">V. albida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having all white, not yellowish, vestiture, except for black hair and scales on the head only. 
<taxonomicName box="[406,517,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albida">
<emphasis box="[406,517,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">V. albida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has black hair on the prosternum and pleura; the wing is completely hyaline and without a yellowish infuscation in the costal cell and at the base; white not brownish squama; legs brown with white scales, not black with brownish­white scales. There is no distinct patagium as is usual in 
<taxonomicName box="[878,930,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[878,930,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">Villa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. The genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1175,1247,404,430]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 6" captionStartId="5.[264,382,1571,1595]" captionTargetBox="[374,1176,520,1570]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[332,1284,504,1593]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 6. Male genitalia: 3. V. aegyptiaca Engel, lateral view; 4. V. bivirgata Austen: a. lateral view, b. tip of epiphallus; 5. V. cana Meigen: a. lateral view, b. tip of epiphallus; 6. V. micrargyra (Walker), lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171553/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[1232,1247,404,430]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) were dissected and are unlike those of 
<taxonomicName box="[706,890,444,469]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="efflatouni">
<emphasis box="[706,890,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">Villa efflatouni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a simple flat spatulate epiphallus and a U­shaped gonostylus. We conclude that it is a distinct species and not a variety of 
<taxonomicName box="[389,495,524,549]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albida">
<emphasis box="[389,495,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">V. albida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We hesitate to suggest that it be placed in a new genus pending the examination of further specimens including the spermathecae of females.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
